National Cohesion and Integration Commission chairman Francis ole Kaparo (pictured) has warned politicians against inciting Kenyans ahead of the General Election.He urged politicians to unite the people. Kaparo urged voters not to allow politicians to divide them. He spoke on Saturday during a fundraiser at Mirango Ongalo Secondary School in Rarieda constituency. Present were Commission on Administrative Justice chairman Otiende Amolo, Judicial Service Commissioner Tom Ojienda and NCIC commissioners Linda Ochiel and Morris Dzoro. Every citizen has a right to stay in any part of this country, so do not be intimidated, Kaparo said. Last week, he defended the commission against claims of ineptitude and accused Kenyans of fueling tribalism. Kaparo urged the youth to preach peace.